This script is a Twitter bot that scrapes blog post content from a website and posts it on Twitter. 
The bot uses Tweepy library for Twitter API interaction and BeautifulSoup library for web scraping.

Functions:

scrape_website(): 
Scrapes the website to retrieve blog post content. It returns a list of dictionaries, where each dictionary represents a blog post with keys 'title', 'url', and 'body'.

post_to_twitter(post, remaining_time): 
Posts a blog post on Twitter and removes it from the list. It takes a dictionary containing the blog post information and the remaining time until the next post.

main(): 
The main function that runs the Twitter bot. It defines the post and rescrape intervals and executes the scraping, posting, and sleeping logic based on the specified intervals and end time.